<DOC><DOCNO> AP880420-0225 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-20-88 0236EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i BC-LebanonText     04-20 0200</FIRST><SECOND>BC-Lebanon Text,0202</SECOND><HEAD>Text of Kidnappers' Statement Threatening Violence</HEAD><HEAD>With AM-Lebanon-Hostages</HEAD><DATELINE>BEIRUT, Lebanon (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Following is the text of the message froma pro-Iranian group holding American captives in Lebanon. It wasdelivered in Arabic and translated by The Associated Press:   The Revolutionary Justice Organization is watching thedevelopments of the Kuwaiti plane hijacking with reassurance andpraises the wisdom and strength of the hijackers. It also supportstheir just demands. We call on our brothers to persevere firmlywithout making any concessions until the goals of the hijacking arerealized because no one can undertake any negative actions againstyou as the hostages' lives will be in danger, not to mention allother possibilities.   We caution the Algerian government, which has mediated for therelease of some French hostages, against any violation or deceptionin its dealings with the hijackers of the Kuwaiti plane becausethere will be total retaliation which will not stop at Kuwait'sborder or Algeria's airport.   The Revolutionary Justice Organiztion declares that it will notsit back and watch America's aggressions in the gulf. There will beretaliations and retaliations to punish the aggressors and makethem understand they will regret their actions.</TEXT></DOC>